@startuml
title HPA + KEDA Scaling Strategy

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

queue "Kafka Topics" as Kafka

cloud "Prometheus" as Prometheus

component "KEDA" as KEDA
component "HPA" as HPA

component "ScaledObject" as ScaledObject

node "Risk Assessment Deployment" as Deployment

component "Pod-1" as Pod1
component "Pod-2" as Pod2
component "Pod-N" as PodN

node "Cluster Autoscaler" as CA

node "Worker Node A" as NodeA
node "Worker Node B" as NodeB
node "Worker Node N" as NodeN

Kafka --> KEDA : Consumer Lag

KEDA --> ScaledObject

ScaledObject --> Deployment

Prometheus --> HPA : CPU\nMemory\nTPS

HPA --> Deployment

Deployment --> Pod1
Deployment --> Pod2
Deployment --> PodN

Pod1 --> NodeA
Pod2 --> NodeB
PodN --> NodeN

Deployment --> CA : More Capacity Needed

CA --> NodeN : Add Nodes

note right of HPA

Infrastructure Metrics

CPU

Memory

TPS

end note

note right of KEDA

Business Metrics

Kafka Lag

Pending Events

Topic Throughput

end note

note bottom

Scaling Flow

Kafka Lag
      ↓
     KEDA
      ↓
 Deployment
      ↓
    Pods

CPU / Memory
      ↓
      HPA
      ↓
 Deployment

No Capacity
      ↓
Cluster Autoscaler
      ↓
New Nodes

end note
@enduml